{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-aa5639016806",
  "content": "eceive pre-extracted text as `source`. The actual PDF byte reading + text extraction happens in the ingestion layer (IngestionAdapter reads the bytes and calls `pdf_extract::extract_text`). This keeps the `ChunkingStrategy` trait synchronous and pure-text.\n\n**Step 3: Register module and run tests to verify they fail**\n\nAdd to `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`:\n```rust\npub mod chunking_pdf;\n```\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pdf -- --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL\n\n**Step 4: Implement PdfChunker**\n\nChunk algorithm:\n1. Split on `\\n\\n` for paragraph boundaries\n2. Filter empty paragraphs\n3. Set `chunk_type = \"paragraph\"`\n\nAdditionally: provide a public helper function `extract_pdf_text(bytes: &[u8]) -> Result<String>` that wraps `pdf_extract::extract_text_from_mem()` for use by ingestion adapters. This function handles errors gracefully (returns an error for encrypted/scanned PDFs).\n\n**Step 5: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pdf -- --nocapture`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_pdf.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs crates/corvia-kernel/Cargo.toml\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.3): PdfChunker — PDF paragraph-level chunking (D68)\"\n```\n\n---\n",
